def check_for_lab(string)
  if /lab/ =~ string
    puts string
  else
    puts "This word doesn't contain lab"
  end
end

check_for_lab("laboratory")
check_for_lab("experiment")
check_for_lab("Pans Labyrinth")
check_for_lab("elaborate")
check_for_lab("polar bear")

Nothing is printed to the screen, the block never sees a .call method. Returns a Proc object

Exception handling deals with errors in a manageable way. It allows the program to continue to function despite the error.

def execute(&block)
  block.call
end

execute { puts "Hello from inside the execute method!" }

